The article is about President Biden expressing his gratitude to Ron Klain for his service as the White House Chief of Staff and welcoming Jeff Zients as his replacement. Biden praises Klain for his intelligence, dedication, and ability to assemble a diverse and talented team. He highlights their accomplishments in fighting COVID, reviving the economy, addressing climate change, and advancing civil rights. Biden believes that Klain's legacy will be the progress made under his leadership. He introduces Jeff Zients as someone who understands the importance of leading a team and getting things done. Biden describes Zients' experience in government, including his successful management of healthcare.gov and leading the COVID response. He expresses confidence in Zients continuing Klain's example of smart and steady leadership. Biden also thanks Klain's family for their commitment and announces an official transition event to thank Klain and welcome Zients to the White House.